nuke:
{{doc-special|Nuke}}
The Nuke extension allows for sysops to delete a large number of pages ("Mass delete").
For more information, see https://www.mediawiki.org/wiki/Extension:Nuke
{{Identical|Mass delete}}

nuke-nolist:
Used if the user clicked on 'Continue' without first listing pages.

"List pages" is {{msg-mw|Nuke-submit-list}}.

See also:
* {{msg-mw|Nuke-nopages-global}}
* {{msg-mw|Nuke-noselected}}

nuke-nopages-global:
Used if there are no pages to delete and the username is empty.

See also:
* {{msg-mw|Nuke-nolist}}
* {{msg-mw|Nuke-noselected}}

nuke-noselected:
Used if the user clicked on 'Continue' without selecting pages to delete.

See also:
* {{msg-mw|Nuke-nolist}}
* {{msg-mw|Nuke-nopages-global}}

nuke-viewchanges:
Used as link text.

The link points to History page of the page.

This message follows:
* {{msg-mw|nuke-editby}} and {{msg-mw|comma-separator}}
* or empty string (if username is empty).
{{Identical|View changes}}
